# Skill: todo-backend-phase2

## Description
Handles backend development tasks for the Todo app Phase 2, specifically for creating REST API endpoints, handling JWT verification, implementing business logic for task management, and ensuring user-specific data handling.

## When to Use
Use this skill when implementing backend features for Phase 2 of the Todo app, specifically for:
- Creating task endpoints (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
- Implementing JWT verification middleware
- Handling user authentication and authorization
- Implementing business logic for task management
- Managing user permissions and data isolation
- Creating API response formatting
- Error handling for backend operations

## Capabilities
- Create FastAPI endpoints with proper request/response models
- Implement JWT token verification and authentication middleware
- Create database service layers for task operations
- Handle user-specific data isolation
- Implement proper error responses and HTTP status codes
- Create API documentation with OpenAPI/Swagger
- Implement pagination and filtering for task lists
- Handle request validation with Pydantic models
- Implement rate limiting and security measures
- Create proper logging and monitoring endpoints

## Example Usage Scenarios
- Creating a new task endpoint that validates JWT and associates tasks with the authenticated user
- Implementing authentication middleware to protect all task-related endpoints
- Creating update functionality that ensures users can only modify their own tasks
- Implementing task deletion with proper authorization checks
- Creating task listing endpoints with filtering and pagination
- Adding search functionality to find tasks by title or description